<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.digital50.com/news/items/BW/2001/07/14/20070816005037/dungeons-dragonsr-flashes-4-ward-at-gen-con.html" class="external text" title="http://www.digital50.com/news/items/BW/2001/07/14/20070816005037/dungeons-dragonsr-flashes-4-ward-at-gen-con.html" rel="nofollow">"Dungeons &amp; Dragons(R) Flashes 4-ward at Gen Con"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.digital50.com/news/items/BW/2001/07/14/20070816005037/dungeons-dragonsr-flashes-4-ward-at-gen-con.html" class="external free" title="http://www.digital50.com/news/items/BW/2001/07/14/20070816005037/dungeons-dragonsr-flashes-4-ward-at-gen-con.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.digital50.com/news/items/BW/2001/07/14/20070816005037/dungeons-dragonsr-flashes-4-ward-at-gen-con.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-10-31</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Dungeons+%26+Dragons%28R%29+Flashes+4-ward+at+Gen+Con&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.digital50.com%2Fnews%2Fitems%2FBW%2F2001%2F07%2F14%2F20070816005037%2Fdungeons-dragonsr-flashes-4-ward-at-gen-con.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Role-playing_game"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-rpgoverview-6">^ <a href="#cite_ref-rpgoverview_6-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-rpgoverview_6-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFRilstone1994">Rilstone, Andrew (1994). <a href="http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/rpgoverview.html" class="external text" title="http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/rpgoverview.html" rel="nofollow">"Role-Playing Games: An Overview"</a> (HTML). RPGnet<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/rpgoverview.html" class="external free" title="http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/rpgoverview.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/rpgoverview.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-01</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Role-Playing+Games%3A+An+Overview&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Rilstone&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrew&amp;rft.au=Rilstone%2C+Andrew&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.pub=RPGnet&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.rpg.net%2Foracle%2Fessays%2Frpgoverview.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Role-playing_game"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><i><a href="/wiki/Werewolf:_The_Apocalypse" title="Werewolf: The Apocalypse">Werewolf: The Apocalypse</a> (2nd Edition)</i>. <a href="/wiki/White_Wolf" title="White Wolf">White Wolf</a>. 1994. pp.&#160;Chapter 1. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1565041127" class="internal">ISBN 1-56504-112-7</a>.  "Although Werewolf is a game, it is more concerned with storytelling than it is with winning. Werewolf is a tool enabling you to become involved in tales of passion and glory, and to help tell those stories yourself."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BWerewolf%3A+The+Apocalypse%5D%5D+%282nd+Edition%29&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3BChapter+1&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BWhite+Wolf%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=1-56504-112-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Role-playing_game"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><i><a href="/wiki/GURPS" title="GURPS">GURPS</a> (4th Edition)</i>. <a href="/wiki/Steve_Jackson_Games" title="Steve Jackson Games">Steve Jackson Games</a>. 2004. pp.&#160;Chapter 1.  "But roleplaying is not purely educational. It's also one of the most creative possible entertainments. Most entertainment is passive: the audience just sits and watches, without taking part in the creative process. In roleplaying, the "audience" joins in the creation. The GM is the chief storyteller, but the players are responsible for portraying their characters. If they want something to happen in the story, they make it happen, because they're in the story."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BGURPS%5D%5D+%284th+Edition%29&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3BChapter+1&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BSteve+Jackson+Games%5D%5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Role-playing_game"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><i><a href="/wiki/Dungeons_%26_Dragons" title="Dungeons &amp; Dragons">Dungeons &amp; Dragons</a></i> <a href="/wiki/Player%27s_Handbook" title="Player's Handbook">Player's Handbook</a> <i>(4th Edition)</i>. <a href="/wiki/Wizards_of_the_Coast" title="Wizards of the Coast">Wizards of the Coast</a>. June 6, 2008. pp.&#160;Chapter 1. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0786948671" class="internal">ISBN 0-7869-4867-1</a>.  "A roleplaying game is a storytelling game that has elements of the games of make-believe that many of us played as children."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BDungeons+%26+Dragons%5D%5D+%27%27%5B%5BPlayer%27s+Handbook%5D%5D%27%27+%284th+Edition%29&amp;rft.date=June+6%2C+2008&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3BChapter+1&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BWizards+of+the+Coast%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0-7869-4867-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Role-playing_game"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFWaskulLust2004">Waskul, Dennis; Lust, Matt (2004). "<a href="http://www.colorado.edu/ibs/pb/thornberry/socy5031/pdfs/waskul_lust_role_playing.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.colorado.edu/ibs/pb/thornberry/socy5031/pdfs/waskul_lust_role_playing.pdf" rel="nofollow">Role-Playing and Playing Roles: The Person, Player, and Persona in Fantasy Role-Playing</a>". <i>Caliber</i> <b>27</b> (3): 333–356. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1525%2Fsi.2004.27.3.333" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1525%2Fsi.2004.27.3.333" rel="nofollow">10.1525/si.2004.27.3.333</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.colorado.edu/ibs/pb/thornberry/socy5031/pdfs/waskul_lust_role_playing.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.colorado.edu/ibs/pb/thornberry/socy5031/pdfs/waskul_lust_role_playing.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.colorado.edu/ibs/pb/thornberry/socy5031/pdfs/waskul_lust_role_playing.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-12-23</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Role-Playing+and+Playing+Roles%3A+The+Person%2C+Player%2C+and+Persona+in+Fantasy+Role-Playing&amp;rft.jtitle=Caliber&amp;rft.aulast=Waskul&amp;rft.aufirst=Dennis&amp;rft.au=Waskul%2C+Dennis&amp;rft.au=Lust%2C+Matt&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=27&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=333%E2%80%93356&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1525%2Fsi.2004.27.3.333&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.colorado.edu%2Fibs%2Fpb%2Fthornberry%2Fsocy5031%2Fpdfs%2Fwaskul_lust_role_playing.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Role-playing_game"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-wherewevebeen-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-wherewevebeen_11-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/wherewevebeen.html" class="external text" title="http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/wherewevebeen.html" rel="nofollow">"Where we've been and where we're going"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/wherewevebeen.html" class="external free" title="http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/wherewevebeen.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.rpg.net/oracle/essays/wherewevebeen.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Where+we%27ve+been+and+where+we%27re+going&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.rpg.net%2Foracle%2Fessays%2Fwherewevebeen.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Role-playing_game"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>: "Generation 1" games</li>
<li id="cite_note-gygaxinterview-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-gygaxinterview_12-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.atlasofadventure.com/Archive/gygaxinterview.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.atlasofadventure.com/Archive/gygaxinterview.asp" rel="nofollow">Interview with Gary Gygax</a> at Atlas of Adventure</li>
<li id="cite_note-cardwell-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-cardwell_13-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.rpgstudies.net/cardwell/attacks.html" class="external text" title="http://www.rpgstudies.net/cardwell/attacks.html" rel="nofollow">The Attacks on Roleplaying Games</a> - originally from the <i>Skeptical Inquirer</i></li>
