<li id="cite_note-chick-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-chick_16-0" title="">^</a></b> "<a href="http://www.chick.com/reading/tracts/0046/0046_01.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.chick.com/reading/tracts/0046/0046_01.asp" rel="nofollow">Dark Dungeons</a>", a <a href="/wiki/Jack_Chick" title="Jack Chick" class="mw-redirect">Jack Chick</a> comic tract portraying D&amp;D as the "Filth of Satan" and promoting <a href="/wiki/Book_burning" title="Book burning">book burning</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.darkshire.net/jhkim/rpg/copyright/cases/tsr_vs_mayfair.html" class="external text" title="http://www.darkshire.net/jhkim/rpg/copyright/cases/tsr_vs_mayfair.html" rel="nofollow">TSR, Inc. v. Mayfair Games, Inc.</a>, No. 91 C 0417 (1993).</li>
<li id="cite_note-tidwell-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-tidwell_18-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.gamecabinet.com/news/TSRWotC.html" class="external text" title="http://www.gamecabinet.com/news/TSRWotC.html" rel="nofollow">Wizards of the Coast to acquire TSR</a>, Ken Tidwell April 10, 1997</li>
